    <h3>GeoJSON</h3>

    <p><strong>/v1/layer/:id/geojson</strong></p>
    Options:
    <ul>
        <li><strong>pid</strong> (required) -- period ID</li>
        <li><strong>box</strong> (optional) -- coordinates of a bounding box, bottom-left and top-right points (formatted as "x1,y1,x2,y2", or "west,south,east,north")</li>
        <li><strong>z</strong> (optional) -- zoom level of map for geometry simplification</li>
    </ul>
    <code>
        GET api.atlastory.com/v1/layer/61/geojson?pid=1&box=-86.309,16.805,-71.631,25.324
    </code>

    <p>
        <em>Example:</em> <a href="/v1/layer/61/geojson?pid=1&z=0">GeoJSON with zoom</a><br/>
        <em>Example:</em> <a href="/v1/layer/61/geojson?pid=1&box=-86.30859375,16.804541076383455,-71.630859375,25.3241665257384">GeoJSON with bounding box</a>
    </p>

    <h3>TopoJSON</h3>

    <p><strong>/v1/layer/:id/topojson</strong></p>
    Options: same as GeoJSON
    <p>
        <em>Example:</em> <a href="/v1/layer/61/topojson?pid=1&box=-86.309,16.805,-71.631,25.324">TopoJSON with bounding box</a>
    </p>

